# Code Style

Match **Prettier** config: no semicolons, double quotes, 2-space indent, trailing commas (ES5). Run `bun run format` if needed; don't fight Prettier.

Match **ESLint** (`@tanstack/eslint-config`) — don't disable rules to silence issues you introduced.

## TypeScript

- `strict` is on — no `any` unless unavoidable; prefer narrowing and explicit types.
- Use `import type` for type-only imports (`verbatimModuleSyntax` is enabled).
- Prefer `undefined` / optional properties over `| null` unless the API already uses null.
- Don't use non-null assertions (`!`) unless the invariant is obvious and local.

## React components

- Use `function` declarations for components (matches existing code).
- Destructure props in the signature.
- Hooks at the top of the component body; no conditional hooks.
- Named exports for components and utilities (`export { Button }`, `export const Route = …`).
- Colocate small route-only components in the route file; extract to `src/components/` when reused.

```tsx
// bad — behaviour encoded in branches
if (status === "online") {
  return <GreenDot />
} else if (status === "offline") {
  return <RedDot />
}

// good — variant prop or small dedicated components
<StatusIndicator status={status} />
```

## Imports

- Use `@/` alias (`@/components/ui/button`, `@/lib/utils`).
- Don't reorder imports to satisfy a personal style — this project has import ordering rules off.

## Styling

- Merge classes with `cn()` — never string-concatenate conflicting Tailwind classes.
- Use CVA (`class-variance-authority`) for components with multiple visual variants (see `button.tsx`).
- Prefer Tailwind utilities over custom CSS. Add to `styles.css` only for theme tokens, base layers, or genuinely global rules.

## Logic density

- No blank lines between trivial adjacent steps in a function.
- No useless variables used only once on the next line.
- Don't extract a function or hook called from exactly one place unless it clarifies intent.
- Return expressions directly when concise; use a variable when it aids readability.

## Control flow

Always use braces for `if`, `else`, `for`, `while` — even for single-statement bodies.

## Comments

Skip comments for obvious boilerplate (simple components, straightforward overrides, prop passthrough).

Add comments when behaviour is non-obvious: side effects, TanStack Router loader/action contracts, SSR constraints, or workarounds worth knowing.

## Performance

- Don't memoize by default (`useMemo`, `useCallback`, `React.memo`) — add only when there's a measured or obvious re-render problem.
- Avoid fetching the same data in multiple sibling components; lift to a route loader or shared hook.
- Prefer one pass over a collection rather than multiple iterations.

## Generated and config files

- Don't hand-edit `routeTree.gen.ts`.
- Theme and design tokens live in `src/styles.css` — extend CSS variables there, not scattered inline styles.
